## Core Architecture — Non-Negotiable Constraints

1. Local-first: SQLite via sql.js as primary data store, works fully offline
2. End-to-end encrypted: Argon2id key derivation from password locally,
   libsodium XSalsa20-Poly1305 for data encryption, key never transmitted
3. Optional encrypted sync to AWS S3 — only ciphertext reaches the server
4. React + TypeScript frontend (Vite)
5. BIP39 24-word recovery phrase at account creation — never held by Liber Praxis
6. Designed to wrap into Tauri desktop app in a later phase
7. No analytics inside the application — Simple Analytics on marketing site only
8. Opt-in error reporting via Sentry with aggressive data scrubbing, off by default

