## What Has Been Built

### LP-01 — Encryption Layer ✅
Files in `src/crypto/`:
- `keyDerivation.ts` — Argon2id key derivation, 64MB memory, 3 iterations, 32-byte output
- `encryption.ts` — libsodium XSalsa20-Poly1305 secretbox, explicit constants (KEY=32, NONCE=24, MAC=16), ensureSodiumReady() pattern
- `recoveryPhrase.ts` — BIP39 24-word phrase generation and key reconstruction
- Tests for all three — 20 passing

Note: test environment requires setup shims for argon2-browser and
libsodium-wrappers (Node.js/ESM compatibility). These are test harness
fixes only, not production code changes. Tracked as technical debt.

### LP-02 — Database Layer 🔄 (built, pending commit)
Files in `src/database/`:
- `schema.ts` — TypeScript types and SQL schema for tables: accounts, clients, sessions, documents
- `db.ts` — sql.js initialization, table creation, Dexie/IndexedDB persistence
- `encryptedStorage.ts` — generic encrypted read/write using crypto layer
- `accountRepository.ts` — account-specific repository using encryptedStorage
- Tests for encryptedStorage and accountRepository
- `src/types/sqljs.d.ts` — minimal sql.js type declaration

Status: 30 tests passing. Bug identified in `accountRepository.ts` upsert method —
the `??` operator treats null and undefined identically, preventing callers from
explicitly clearing fields. Fix in progress.

